taglist-plus.vim
================

This is a fork of the popular taglist.vim plugin.

Taglist-plus provides excellent Javascript support via jsctags. See this post
for examples:

    http://discontinuously.com/2011/03/vim-support-javascript-taglist-plus/

This plugin can also be obtained from github:

    https://github.com/int3/vim-taglist-plus

Installation
------------

Unzip the files to your `.vim` directory.

Taglist-plus requires jsctags for enhanced Javascript functionality. Jsctags
can be obtained via github:

    https://github.com/mozilla/doctorjs

Jsctags requires a recent version of node.js -- the default one provided in
Maverick Meerkat won't cut it. You can build it from source:

    http://nodejs.org/#download

or get it via this PPA:

    https://launchpad.net/~richarvey/+archive/nodester

If you're going the PPA route, you'll need to map `nodejs` to `node`. Here are
the commands:
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:richarvey/nodester
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install nodejs
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/local/bin/node

Usage
-----

`:TlistToggle` brings up the taglist window.  More commands can be found via
`:help taglist-commands`.

